The Federal Government has declared Friday, April 15, and Monday, April 18 as public holidays to mark this year’s Good Friday and Easter celebration. Interior Minister Rauf Aregbesola, on behalf of the Federal Government, announced this in a statement yesterday in Abuja. In the statement by the Permanent Secretary in the ministry, Dr. Shuaib Belgore, the minister urged Christians to emulate the attributes of sacrifice, togetherness, forgiveness, kindness, love, peace and patience in celebrating Easter.   Inheritance : Court orders Ndubuisi Kanu’s widow to serve…     Umahi’s presidential bid on course, says aide     Nigeria about to acquire more territory in Gulf of Guinea,…   He noted that such attributes were among the practices of Jesus Christ, as exemplified by His ministry on earth. Aregbesola urged Christians and other Nigerians to use this year’s Easter celebration to pray for an end to all security challenges bedevilling the country. The minister assured Nigerians that the Federal Government would ensure that the recent attacks by criminals on the highways, airport and the railway were timely brought to an end. “Security is everybody’s business. I, therefore, urge Nigerians and foreigners resident in our country to display a high sense of citizenship and public spiritedness at this critical time in the history of our country, by supporting the efforts of all security agencies in bringing peace and security of lives and property of the citizenry,” he said.